(firstQuint)Effect of Pentoxifylline on Tight Junctions (TJs) of Intestinal Mucosa in Patients With Irritable Bowel Syndrome(IBS).

 Disruption of the intestinal epithelial barrier is part of the pathophysiology of IBS favoring immune activation present in the mucosa of these patients and the development of symptoms in IBS.

 To evaluate the effect of treatment with pentoxifylline (PTX) in patients with IBS related to clinical response and modulation of the components of the epithelial barrier at the level of intestinal mucosa.

